courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:
• stimulate self-reflection and achieve self-understanding through experiential activities;
• identify their roles and expectations as an individual, a student of SHHO and CUHK, as well as a global citizen;
• develop an appreciation of their position and opportunities being members of the college and university;
• enhance their self-confidence in initiating and developing works and projects that contribute to personal development; and
• foster valuable experience working with students and staff of different backgrounds.

Upon completion of this course, students are expected to be able to:

* demonstrate the ability to identify, synthesise and generate ideas in response to social problems;
* collaborate and exchange insights and knowledge with peers through group work;
* enhance their sense of empathy, social responsibility, and commitment to caring for other stakeholders in the community;
* recognise the community’s needs and real-life situations of the vulnerable groups, particularly those related to the selected SDGs of No Poverty, Good Health and Well-being, Quality Education, Reducing Inequality, and Climate Action.

Upon completion of this course, students are expected to be able to:

* re-examine their personal development through self-discovery and self-reflection;
* enhance interpersonal and employability skills through service activities and group work;
* develop a stronger sense of citizenship in terms of empathy and caring for other stakeholders in the community;
* reflect on the community’s needs and real-life situations of the vulnerable groups, particularly those related to the selected SDGs of No Poverty, Good Health and Well-being, Quality Education, Reducing Inequality, and Climate Action.

Upon completion of this course, students are expected to be able to:
• understand the different perspectives about the meaning of life and work;
• develop appreciation of the many possibilities of work, as well as the variety of aspirations and ambitions for life among fellow students;
• re-examine their assumptions and aspirations of life and career planning as a result.
